{"ts":"2026-06-27T07:17:25.116Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Considering Component Integration**\n\nI'm currently exploring the architecture of the dashboard layout. I've noted the `DataTable` component's location. Now, I'm evaluating integrating components directly or building a fully customized local dashboard. The potential for a custom dashboard layout is looking promising.\n\n\n**Designing Billing Page**\n\nI've decided to fully rewrite `/admin/billing` as a dedicated internal billing and invoice management preview page. The existing `page.tsx` will be replaced, allowing for a focused interface. It will contain an invoice list, preview elements for client, project, amount, due date, and status. It must offer filters for client, status, and month, and include the 'Create invoice preview' action.\n\n\n**Defining Invoice Properties**\n\nI'm now detailing the individual invoice properties for the mock billing system. I've pinpointed key data points: client, project, amount (with currency considerations), due date, status, and invoice ID. I'm leaning toward defining a local mock data list using `useState` for filterable invoice previews and will explore building an accompanying high-fidelity mockup database.\n\n\n**Drafting Invoice Preview Logic**\n\nNow, I'm focusing on the functionality of the invoice preview creation. The goal is to ensure that when a preview is made, it's added to a local list of invoices to test features like filtering and dynamic dashboard updates. This interactive approach aligns with our quality goals. I will be drafting the internal design plan per the request, which includes a detailed internal design plan to be drafted, covering things like page narrative, visual metaphor, and interaction strategy.\n\n\n**Visualizing Invoice Ledger**\n\nI'm now thinking about the visual presentation for financial auditing clarity. I'm imagining a \"high-trust cryptographic ledger\" visual metaphor, implementing a terminal-inspired UI with glowing security cues, clean typography, and SVG diagrams. The color palette will be charcoal with neon blue, teal, or emerald highlights. Layout-wise, there will be a premium header with title, description, and \"Draft Invoice Preview\" button.\nThe plan also includes summary cards with micro-sparklines, an adaptive filter section, and a responsive ledger table containing key invoice details.\n\n\n**Planning Invoice UI Features**\n\nI'm now detailing the UI interactions and features for the billing page's invoice preview functionality. I'm focusing on a slide-over panel for drafting new invoices, including input fields for client, project, amount, due date, status, and month. Clicking \"Generate Cryptographic Draft\" will add it to the React state. Furthermore, a detail panel for selected invoices will reveal a \"Cryptographic Ledger Attestation\", mock SHA signatures, billing breakdown, and a \"Download Receipt Preview\" action. I'm also planning soft hover interactions, modal animations, live filtering, and a simulated \"Cryptographic sealing\" effect.\n\n\n"}}
